Everything as it is now
August 30, 2013 mcpherson Leave a comment
Walking idly through the walkways of a learning institute on a Friday, a strong narrative voice running through my head, envisioning this writing, stuck in a loop of doom and gloom, distinctly repeating the words, ‘was I made for more than this?’ The boy who loved pretending, loved company and acting out the stage, being the class clown just to make everyone’s day. Now he sits at a desk, years gone by, reading re-writing and answering questions, hunched over in a corner of a library, in silence. Three days gone by, all in quiet, only words uttered to parents about assignments. In and out of campus/home and hardly any progress, days spent wondering ‘was I meant for more than this?’

I sit at this desk, peering out the window, things seem foggy without the glasses I haven’t got around to repairing. I grab a book on entrepreneurship, maybe for a sense of identity, it sits on the table closed and dormant before me. Communication assignment in two days, I’ve scarcely begun, the ‘role model’ of my Comm lecturer, has demonstrated who I most certainly do not want to become. An unenthusiastic, shallow thinking, bearded and dishevelled man that paces the room, talking of vague grand topics and how the general public just consumes. My mind once again begs the question ‘was I made for more than this?’

A three year plan, what for? 20k down the drain, depression and an ‘I have an education’ ticket to show to an employer? Disagreeing with lecturers in first year, It looks like I have a bright future as a sheep, to follow my shepherd and occasionally make a peep. I return to this campus, to feel like I have somewhere to belong, sitting at the café, drinking an ice coffee, surrounded by foreign conversations. I walk through the ground, to get a pair of headphones, expressionless, no hints of emotion, a psychology student aware of how to mask all feeling. The voice persists, ‘was I made for more than this?’ Approaching the counter, I remember that I don’t have a dime, I spent it on food and coffee, just part of the daily grind.

The happenings of a grossly unimportant person
August 28, 2013 mcpherson Leave a comment
Questions no-one asked

Why did I start blogging?

I wanted to express my thoughts and self in a way that was not otherwise possible in the physical realm. I realised in late highschool that I actually enjoyed writing exam essays and sharing my ideas in this text form which is relatively effortless for me. After my gap year I had a head full of amazing stories (or so I thought) that I wanted to share and for people to get a laugh out of. I also wanted to discuss ideas I had in a public form, as opposed to a privatised diary. I suppose there was also some vanity and egotism involved also, after all, to write a blog you have to think to some degree that what you have to say is worth reading.

How is my experience at University?

I’m figuring out that opinions, views and delusions of grandeur our counter productive here. Sometimes I feel insulted by the absolutely basic level of some of the first year material. Some lectures I swear, just watched a 15 minute video on the topic they were supposedly teaching and summarized it poorly in 40 minutes. I could have done a better job and been more enthusiastic about it. A PHD apparently is a badge of infallibility. I have something like 1-2 hours a day on uni and the rest is ‘fuck off and do an assignment’ time.

Socially, to be very honest, it seems that most people are really not interested in being friends or anything more really. In this cocooned society most people keep to themselves and don’t bother leaving their comfort zones. If you do, as I have a couple of times, there isn’t any amazing result. Just some brief excitement then right back to where you started discouraging you from ever even bothering to talk outside of a tutorial. NoFap isn’t helping (refer to previous post). It’s like women don’t want you, and now neither does old righty. It’s a very lonely and isolated place apart from the 3-4 ‘legacy’ friends you have known for years who help to keep you sane. I’ve been participating, doing my reading and attending lectures and things still seem mediocre. Feeling more and more like Darrel the Disappointed Pug.

I just swallowed my last oxiracetam pill and downed a strong coffee and that’s just motivation enough to keep the ball rolling on this blog. After all, it’s practice for the creative writing course I do. So yeah, now this is actually study. I don’t know how I feel about that. I will want to add more to this, but for now i’m going to post it because I’m far too impatient and demotivated.

Sincerely,

a member of the ‘me’ generation.

NoFap Challenge #Day 3
August 28, 2013 mcpherson Leave a comment
So, basically my friends and I agreed on a little challenge… And that is to, well, not ‘fap.’ Hence the title.

The guidelines are as follows:

“no masturbation at all
no pornographic material what so ever
no ‘edging’, do you know what i mean by that?
its when you get close to finishing but you don’t, that counts as breaking the streak”

The winner receives a six pack of alcoholic beverage from all of the participants.

So far no one has admitted to cracking and fallen into venial sin. Unfortunately for me, I can’t afford to loose… Literally. I have less than $5.00 AUD, so I suppose i’m in for the long haul sigh.

Why are we doing this? I don’t exactly know. One of my friends believed that there were benefits, changes that occur in the body when you refrain from such ‘unnatural deeds.’ I don’t think any of us have gone longer than a week abstaining from this since we hit adolescence, so it seems an almost insurmountable feat. I’ve read similar articles on the topic where participants report higher confidence/aggression a need to approach talk to women, as well as a level of indifference towards the opposite gender… pfft yeah, if you says so.

“The night is always darkest just before the dawn” – The Dark Knight

I thought this quote best described the struggles of the challenge… Until I realised the mornings were even worse.

>

I am currently on day 3. (It doesn’t sound like a long time, but it’s like dog years..)

What I have noticed:

Decreased aggression, less workout motivation, more reliance on stimulants like caffeine and I have had a greater desire for fast food, i suspect this is so I can get the same ‘satisfaction’ and endorphin release. I’m currently drinking my 5th -ish coffee of the day. I feel less emotional overall, and am currently experiencing a light wave of depression. music doesn’t seem to have as much effect on me, in a motivational or ‘moving’ sense. All of these ‘symptoms’ may be of a sort of withdrawal, something like a recovering heroin addict might get… I mean it’s only day 3, but that means that i have missed out on 10-15 ‘doses’ by now. I really don’t know and more test are needed. So far I have approached one female for a five-second conversation… and it’s very possible I would have done that anyway. I expect that before the week is out i will be begging strangers for wristies. Wish me luck.

The Problem Of Free Will
August 25, 2013 mcpherson 1 Comment
Let’s take jar of jellybeans and call it ‘liberty.’

The jellybeans are symbolic of an individuals freedom potential.

Take out a generous handful, this is your genetic predispositions, influencing behaviour and the way others react to your presence.

Take out another generous handful, this is your immediate family environment, you now have morals and expectations weighted on you.

Take out a scoop, this is your general societies values and beliefs, you are now restricted by laws and etiquette.

Take out another scoop, this is media influence from as early as infancy, radio, television, books all influencing your consciousness.

Take out another load, this is the people you meet in your life who are also products of their given environments, this is variable and largely left to chance, but is a heavy influence regardless.

With all these jellybeans removed, are there any left in the jar?

A passing thought.

Memories as good as dreams; the hollow past barely believable. Dont bother reading this
August 12, 2013 mcpherson 6 Comments
James stood on the rooftop overlooking the city, as he had done a thousand times before. Things we’re no different. Cars and bus’ raced along the busy roads, people rushed here and there, planes soared above his head. Life continued as if unshakable. It was as if they didn’t know, or had forgotten. Just over the horizon, half the city had been torn to pieces. Still smoldering, a chunk remained missing, some vital piece, and still the cogs kept turning. Familiar faces now seemed strangers, passers by would lock eyes for a moment, just long enough to see that brief recognition in each others eyes, before departing without an utterance. The cogs kept turning.

Standing at a busy crosswalk, it was difficult to decipher ‘stop’ from ‘go.’ Something that, to him must have once seemed so simple was near incomprehensible. Lines so clear, now seemed blurred. He crossed the street, eyes closed, hearing the screeching tires of the car, he opened his eyes and gasped to see the eyes of his killer before collision. The cogs kept turning.

James stood on the rooftop overlooking the city, as he had done a thousand times before. “Stay” a voice called. He turned to see the contorted face of someone who seemed vaguely familiar. “Why?” The protagonist replied. There was no response, the figure began bawling relentlessly. He watched indifferently. The figure screamed, it’s head expanding as it did so. An audible popping sound could be heard as the holes where it’s ears were began expelling enormous amounts of blood. It’s eyes swelled up as it looked at him with the most sincere pain and indescribable anguish. ‘Pop,’ it’s head splattered as if a rice bubble in milk. He grinned. The city was now missing another great chunk. No one seemed to notice, everyone was far too busy. He jumped off the ledge. The cogs kept turning.

James stood on the rooftop overlooking the city, as he had done a thousand times before. It was time to go home. “Stay” a voice said from behind him. He turned. And Smiled. “Only for you.” She returned his fond gaze and approached, slowly, cautiously. “Don’t be afraid,” he said, “I’ll make sure you don’t fall…” She stepped up the ledge and held his hand. “Soon it will be over,” she whispered. “I know,” he replied. “But we have now, this state or perfection.” They watched the setting sun together. “Goodbye,” she whispered. They jumped. The cogs kept turning.

James stood on the rooftop overlooking the city, as he had done a thousand times before. He leaped from the rooftop taking flight. So little of the city was left, he soared and examined the remains. At that moment, soaring over remains, everything stopped. The cars, the people, the buss’. “I never meant for any of this, I’m sorry, words can’t describe..” Their faces grimaced as he looked down at them. “It’s all too much.” He plummeted to the ground with a ‘splat’. The cogs kept turning.

James stood on the rooftop overlooking the city, as he had done a thousand times before. “Please don’t die on me.” He turned to see a small child. “We don’t want this, you’re better than this.” “I’m trying,” he replied. “There is no solid ground and everything is fantasy. If nothing is true then it follows that everything I have ever been led to believe is in question, if what my eyes perceive is blue but that is only just my brains interpretation of a light pattern, what is to say that it is not the same case with perspectives? There are other colours im not seeing, the truth is not transparent. It is impossible to be an honest man in a world of cruelty, in such a place where virtues are scarce and vice is being ‘open-minded,’ insane, as it were for anyone to comprehend that everything is a perception. What is art to one man is dribble to another. There is no heart in this. The suffering is complete and everything seems to have gone full circle. All that remains are vague memories, little recollections of joy, love, hope, all dashed as we sink further into the ground. But not all of us, a piece, a little bit, while the rest remains stagnant. This is a stream of consciousness, this is rubbish writing, both equally true, both equally wrong. Insanity is doing the same thing over and over again and expecting a different result. This was never meant to last, and it cannot go away. I the villain, all my toils for nothing. I know what it takes to lie, to become disconnected, to give everything. Just to be forgotten. I am no-one and and I am everyone. What makes you more you than I? or I more I than You? Goodbye. Hello. See you later. What’s up, Bye. We’ll be seeing you here again, and we have saved a seat. A special reserve for people such as yourself!”

James stood on the rooftop overlooking the city, as he had done a thousand times before. He raised his hands to the sky watching scarlet raindrops fall from the dark clouds above. Every face as a cloud, all forgotten to the conscious mind, awaiting a glance of recognition. He laughed manically as they whined and moaned leaking their scarlet contents. “Stop” He turned to see a figure–himself. Covered in his own blood and looking like a plague victim, the newcomer pounced. They both fell plummeting through the air. Every breath seemed a pain, every blink a struggle. sdnmlllllsrkrvfnjmkdmlmfv fdj45itrvfo vc

And then someone told you it was all a joke, you’re over-reacting. It’s funny.

James stood on the rooftop overlooking the city, as he had done a thousand times before.

“A dream’s real so long as you’re dreaming, couldn’t you say the same about life?”

The cogs keep turning.

I’m not jealous of your 80,000 and house deposit
September 18, 2013 mcpherson Leave a comment
Long story short, I heard through a friend that another friend of mine has been moving up in the world of real-estate. (19 year old selling houses?? Bizarre) He boasts about his eighty grand saved up in the bank and the “fairy nice” (friend’s words) house that will soon be his to live in. Apparently, he predicts that by his late twenties he will be living comfortably. This is the kind of guy that ‘always has to be the best,’ the kid that always had to be superior in sports who’s dad pushed him harder than anyone else’s. Swimming trials, this guy was in a private lane with his dad as coach, when it came to Tennis, his dad once again chose who he would train with, some people were not ‘good-enough’ to play his gifted son, and now he’s a triathlon champ or something of the like.

So sure, damn, this guy seems great huh? Successful, talented and soon to be living in a nice house before 20! Well, that’s what most people seem to think.

Flash to someone like me; same age, lives at home, Uni on weekdays, unemployed, works out in the mornings, doesn’t really sound quite as prestigious does it? So, I would like to present some different perspectives on this issue.

What is the rush?

Gosh dammit, do you really hate your dad that much? (jokes, that was harsh) You have most of your life to spend paying bills, being independent, making your own meals and doing your own laundry.

Do you even enjoy your job?

I’ve done my fair share of time in mundane, ‘pretend to be friendly’ jobs and gosh darn it I was good, but do you really want to be doing that into your late twenties and beyond??

There is a positive correlation between loss of IQ and your financial gain…

This is a polite way of saying ‘cashed-up-bogan.’ I don’t go to uni for job prospects, I do it out of interest and wanting to ‘know’ more and become ‘more,’ unlike the majority of people or so it seems, who try and drill you into submitting and choosing a career path.

Are you living in the future?

What makes you so sure you will be around to see the sun rise tomorrow? I’ve been watching a lot of Zen Buddhism videos lately, and I feel that every day can be the best day of your life. When you have a house, possessions and independence, you are still fundamentally the same, you don’t simply ‘level up’ to a happier state. You need to be able to feel happy even when there isn’t any amazing reason to be.

If money was no object, what would you be doing?

I think this question needs some re-work. Some people, probably including me don’t really know what they want, and so they make up things when quizzed on it. Sure you want independence and a mortgage or whatever, but then you have to ask ‘why,’ perhaps you have a flawed perception of success, buried in the clutches of capitalism.

Would you find yourself interesting?

I always like to think this. Would you want to talk to yourself? Do you have interesting hobbies, things to say to people, can you have intellectual and jovial conversations, what if you’re always working trying to convince other ‘cashed-up-bogans’ (mining area) to buy products (houses) from you? That dialect must be so colloquial and absolutely boring as piss-ass, study some philosophy ;).

In concluding,

I think that finding your interests, spending time doing things you enjoy and people that are meaningful to you is all that you really need, if you have those things, whether you live in a shoe box or a mansion, you will never be with out. Heck, look at Miley Cyrus, her money sure helped a bunch!

Post #80 or something
September 8, 2013 mcpherson Leave a comment
This blog has more or less transcended into a ‘notepad’ of sorts, this post is no exception. Virtual organisation still remains a lot simpler than anything physical.

So I’m currently starting to write an argument for philosophy that is due tomorrow and I’ve hit a plateau, so I’m going to write here to get a flow of ideas going. I’ve been watching many videos lately by the acclaimed author and ‘renaissance man,’ Timothy Ferris and incorporating methods where possible.

Tips for writing summarised:

-Write everything you want to say, then, just like Michael Angelo, you need to chisel out the masterpiece that readers want. Neil Strauss recommends a third edited copy ‘for the haters.’ Similar to how in 8 mile (Eminem film) he uses all his opponents insults in his own raps and leaves him with no material left to ‘spit.’

-Whenever you need to reference or go back to something but don’t want to interrupt flow, type ‘(pk).’ There are almost no words that have pk in them in the English language so there is no difficulty when ‘ctrl + f’ finding them later.

-’Write as if you were talking to friends you hadn’t seen in a while after 2 drinks’ -Ferris.

-Carry a moleskin or notepad. I don’t do this, I figure that If something is important enough I just repeat it in my minds voice to remember it.

-Hit a wall? Read the work of people with a similar narrative voice and then write as them. For me with the rant blog, I guess I would say that it purely co-incidentally has a similar tone to ‘Dose of Buckley’ or ‘Opinionated Man.’

Tips for learning summarised:

-Be very specific, it makes things easy. For example, ‘I don’t want to learn an entire language, I want to have a conversation with a stranger of that nationality on a bus.’ Therefore, you would focus on the colloquial language and vocalised conversation. Pick an area that interests you, ie programming, figure out what you want to do; ‘build a wordpress theme,’ skim read two books on ‘coding’ and then work on the specific skill.

-Before bed and upon rising are crucial learning times. This is the best way to dramatically learn supposedly. If you play/do ‘X’ before bed, you will be noticeable better at the skill in the morning.

-Make things fun, not a chore. (How you ask? How should I know, what you enjoy!) “A spoonful of sugar helps the medicine go down”- Some old bat who sings in musicals.

Tips for productivity:

-Set tight, but realistic deadlines. Got a week to do the assignment? GIve yourself two days! Or if you’re like most people, you leave yourself only the night before. (what i’m doing right now…) Neil Strauss believes that you need real-world consequences for not reaching these deadlines!

-Two tasks a day max. (according to Four Hour Work Week) People also use a box grid where they choose what is most pressing and do that, but that seems to me like common sense, something that I can just do internally.

-Goals obviously, yet to adopt this. An Entrepreneur book I was reading said that you need milestones towards the big goal etc. Ferris seems to suggest that you just need to have a very specific goal and that uncomplicated everything, whilst still having logical steps to achieve it.

Application called ‘Freedom’ bans internet for specified periods, although i would like to think I have enough self-control not to require it. There is another site ‘Stickk,’ where you need to complete ‘X’ or you have to donate ‘Y’ to an organisation that you hate. Clever idea for a site.

Thoughts on the ‘real-world’:

‘Moot,’ the creator of 4chan, converted a Japanese site to english for his friends to use. It is a non-profit sensation and it’s creator is a poor studying student.

‘PewDiePie, Syndicate, Skyplaysminecraft, created their youtube channels for fun and persisted for approximately 2-4 years. 1 ‘true fan’ a day for 3 years is 1000 ‘true fans.’ If each of those pay $100ea in year in support of your cause = 100k a year.

Steve Jobs, pictured the future and technologies and utilized people and resources to achieve those, not necessarily having the skills himself to build all he envisioned.

The Nike’s motto ‘Just do it,’ was an alteration of a mans last words before execution ‘Let’s just get on with it.’ The fact that I can’t remember his name is testament to the lasting impression such a small person can have on the world.

‘You only live once, you have to do what you love. If your career and finances fall through, you have nothing left in the wold to live for. If you do what you love, it doesn’t matter whether or not you get payed for it, and in the end, you will never be without purpose.’ -very roughly paraphrasing Neil Strauss

Endless rhetoric:
